main event: On November 7, 1957, an unidentified flying object was observed in Dunedin, Florida for seven or eight minutes.
interesting points: The sighting involved a round silvery object the size of a half dollar at arm's length with a pulsing, flashing light.Both military patrols reported seeing an unidentified object near the atomic bomb site in New Mexico.The object reportedly had a tail that was four times as long as it was wide.A college professor described a different bright light moving at an estimated speed of 3-5 times that of a jet aircraft.The investigation concluded the objects observed were unidentified, with some speculating they may have been jets.
sighted object: One round silvery object with a pulsing, flashing light
witness description: A college professor with a background in atmospheric physics.
